--- title: "gender_submission.csv" author: "Choo Jian Yuan" format: html editor: visual --- #### Before use the data for my analysis, preemptive checking has been done and result as per below： ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} # Adjustment done on dataset # 1.Change passenger_id become character instead of numerical # 2.translate survived status in more readable manner where: # S = survive # D = death data1 <- data1 %>% clean_names() %>% mutate (passenger_id = as.character(passenger_id), survived = case_when( survived == 1 ~ "S", survived == 0 ~ "D", TRUE ~ as.character(survived))) ``` ::: ```{=html} ``` ::: {#summaryPanel .table-of-summary} Summary of checking - `passenger_id` column has 418 unique IDs with characters length of 3 to 4 digits. Result show in section - Direct - `survived` column has 2 unique values of D and S. Result show in section - Direct - Full dataset Direct ::: ```{=html} ```

Summary for Dataset

::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} #To double confirm status of changes data1 %>% skim() ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} Table: Data summary | | | |:------------------------|:----------| |Name |Piped data | |Number of rows |418 | |Number of columns |2 | |_______________________ | | |Column type frequency: | | |character |2 | |________________________ | | |Group variables |None | **Variable type: character** |skim_variable | n_missing| complete_rate| min| max| empty| n_unique| whitespace| |:-------------|---------:|-------------:|---:|---:|-----:|--------:|----------:| |passenger_id | 0| 1| 3| 4| 0| 418| 0| |survived | 0| 1| 1| 1| 0| 2| 0| ::: :::

Summary for survived

::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} survived_in_detail <- function(x){ death <- sum(x[,"survived"]=="D") %>% paste0(.," passengers died in the incident") survive <- sum(x[,"survived"]=="S") %>% paste0(.," passengers survived the incident") results <- c(death, survive) return(results) } survived_in_detail(data1) %>% result_display(.,"") ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
Output :

152 passengers survived the incident
